    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's not advisable to have an open RPC port. Whilst we tried to limit the API namespaces callable by default, users may change that, or some attacker might find some funky API call that might not cause damage in itself, but may be an annoyance (e.g. trace transactions, hitting the CPU).\r\n\r\nOur recommendation is to use RPC to talk to the node via your own programs only (or trusted programs) and if you want to expose public functionality over the internet, you should put your own APIs in front which you can control for authentication and rate limiting.",
